`resolveEthSpinFromBox` already has a clean single-spin boundary: it computes `payout`, calls `_distributePayout`, flushes claimable/pool state, then recirculates `lootboxShare`. That means a foil-only pre-branch can be kept out of regular Degenerette settlement if it is keyed off a new foil-specific entrypoint or selector.
